column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Antenna Land > 4898
column7: The members of Antenna Land see little point in spending money on technology beyond the basics. Midscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Bundled Burbs > 4873
column7: Bundled Burbs is the kind of place where no one needs to argue over who gets to use the household computer, cell phone, or TV set. Upscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Calling Circles > 4866
column7: Calling Circles consists of middle-class minorities who like technology more than their midscale budgets allow. Midscale Younger w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Cinemaniacs > 4878
column7: The suburban-based Boomers of Cinemaniacs spend heavily on film entertainment. Many are upscale singles and couples who subscribe to cable TV to indulge their passion for cinema with the convenience of video-on-demand. Upscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Connected Country > 4862
column7: For the upscale families in Connected Country, satellite dishes and cell phones have brought the world to their rural enclaves. Upscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Cyber Sophisticates > 4871
column7: The second wealthiest segment, Cyber Sophisticates is filled with well-educated Boomer couples who've integrated the Internet into their lives. Wealthy Middle Age w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Cyber Strivers > 4881
column7: The working-class families that comprise Cyber Strivers say they'd be early tech adopters, if only they could afford it. Instead, these young minority families manage with older, less expensive technology. Lower Midscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Digital Dreamers > 4890
column7: The lower-middle-class singles and couples in Digital Dreamers are only middling adopters of new technology. Lower Midscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Discounts and Deals > 4904
column7: The members of Discounts & Deals are always looking for a bargain--especially when it comes to technology services. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Gadgets Galore > 4877
column7: The upper-middle-class families in Gadgets Galore may not be the first to embrace new technology, but when they do, they can't get enough. Upper Midscale Older w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Gearing Up > 4891
column7: The youngest of all the Nielsen ConneXions segments, Gearing Up is home to mostly twentysomething singles signing their first telecommunications agreements. Low Income Middle Age w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Generation WiFi > 4865
column7: The young singles and couples who make up Generation WiFi are a footloose group. Midscale Younger w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > High-Tech Society > 4864
column7: High-Tech Society represents the most affluent technology-enabled segment in the nation. Wealthy Older w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > IM Nation > 4886
column7: The young singles and couples in IM Nation stay connected to friends and family thanks to cell phones, having recently severed their landline service. Lower Midscale Younger w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Internet Hinterlands > 4882
column7: Rural and upscale, the members of Internet Hinterlands rely on dish technology to enhance their lives. Upscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Kids and Keyboards > 4874
column7: In Kids & Keyboards, parents spend big on technology to entertain and educate their children. Upper Midscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Last to Adopt > 4910
column7: The poorest Nielsen ConneXions segment is also the one least likely to acquire new technology. Low Income Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Leisurely Adopters > 4901
column7: Given their low incomes and advancing age, the members of Leisurely Adopters keep their technology spending to a minimum by necessity. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Low-Speed Boomers > 4883
column7: Convenience drives the adoption behavior of Low-Speed Boomers. Wealthy, educated, and suburban, these empty-nesting couples typically acquire technology that saves them time and effort. Wealthy Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Low-Tech Country > 4897
column7: The rural couples and singles in Low-Tech Country enjoy the latest advances that technology from the 1970s can offer. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Multimedia Families > 4879
column7: The middle-class households of Multimedia Families are all about kids. They watch kids' shows on TV, play games on the Internet, and operate PSPs and PlayStation IIIs with aplomb. Upper Midscale Older w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > New Kids on the Grid > 4895
column7: The poor, largely middle age and single households that make up New Kids on the Grid have only modest budgets that they can devote to communications technology. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > New Technorati > 4876
column7: NoneThe members of New Technorati are young, footloose, and wireless. These mainly Gen-Y singles and couples rarely leave home without their MP3 players, wireless laptops, and mobile phones. Upper Midscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Old-Time Media > 4903
column7: Tried and true are the hallmarks of technology that appeal to one of the oldest ConneXions segment, Old-Time Media. Upper Midscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Opting Out > 4893
column7: The mature couples in Opting Out can afford to buy the latest technology; they just frequently choose not to. Upper Midscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Plugged-In Families > 4860
column7: Kids rule in Plugged-In Families, so it's no surprise that the technology and media choices here have a child-friendly skew. Upscale Younger w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Rural Transmissions > 4884
column7: When it comes to technology, the members of Rural Transmissions play only one note: satellite dishes. Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Satellite Seniors > 4906
column7: The rural singles and couples in Satellite Seniors have downscale incomes and proportionately modest technology budgets. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Satellites and Silos > 4870
column7: The country couples of Satellites & Silos swear by their dishes. Too isolated for cable or DSL services, these younger, upper-middle income, rural residents rely on satellites for most of their entertainment needs. Upper Midscale Middle Age w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Smart Gamers > 4868
column7: The suburban Boomer families of Smart Gamers like to work hard and play hard; they excel in both working from home and playing games online. Upscale Older w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Tech Nests > 4861
column7: Young, wired families make up Tech Nests, a segment of small-town families with big appetites for consumer electronics. Midscale Younger w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Tech Skeptics > 4899
column7: They may have money and education, but the members of Tech Skeptics are late adopters when it comes to technology. Upper Midscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Tech-Free Frontier > 4908
column7: Who needs computers, the Internet, on-demand movies, or MP3 players? Certainly not the rugged retirees in Tech-Free Frontier. Lower Midscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Technovators > 4859
column7: Rich, educated, and tech-savvy, the members of Technovators lead the nation in acquiring the latest communications and entertainment technology. Wealthy Younger w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Techs and the City > 4887
column7: Concentrated in urban apartment communities, Techs and the City consists of young, cyberspace-savvy singles who spend much of their free time online. Lower Midscale Younger w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Techtown Lites > 4894
column7: The lower-mid residents of Techtown Lites are content to live with only basic communication services. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > The Pragmatics > 4872
column7: The upscale suburbanites in The Pragmatics use technology to simplify their lives.Upscale Younger w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > The Unconnected > 4909
column7: Downscale incomes and advanced ages combine to make for low technology usage in The Unconnected. Downscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > Video Vistas > 4885
column7: The members of Video Vistas love their entertainment on screens. These large, lower-middle-class families like to watch TV programs, play video games, and even download videos off the Internet. Lower Midscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > ConneXions Code > WiFi Warriors > 4869
column7: WiFi Warriors is a segment of wealthy executives and professionals who rely on technology for their travel-intensive jobs. Wealthy Middle Age w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Annuity-ville > 4812
column7: No place has more seniors, fewer children, and a greater passion for fixed-rate annuities than Annuity-ville. Upper Midscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > ATM Nation > 4838
column7: As hip as they are, the members of ATM Nation are, nevertheless, financially unsophisticated. Many of these city apartment dwellers boast midscale incomes and have yet to accumulate appreciable assets. Midscale Younger Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Bargain Lovers > 4821
column7: Call them thrifty or call them economical; just don't call them cheap. Upscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Big Spenders > 4808
column7: The suburban Boomers who comprise Big Spenders are the ultimate financial jugglers. Wealthy Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Bottom-Line Blues > 4857
column7: Bottom-Line Blues is the most financially challenged of all P$YCLE segments. No segment has fewer income-producing assets, and few rank lower when it comes to income or home ownership. Low Income Middle Age Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Business Class > 4802
column7: As the segment most likely to belong to a country club, Business Class is known for its lavish spending style. Upscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Capital Accumulators > 4809
column7: Capital Accumulators is a collection of 55+ year-old suburbanites dedicated to growing their IRAs and 401(k) retirement accounts. Midscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > City Strivers > 4853
column7: Filled with younger apartment dwellers, City Strivers consists mostly of under-35 year olds with lower-middle-class to midscale incomes and few income-producing assets. Midscale Younger Mostly w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Civic Spirits > 4805
column7: They may be retired, but they're not retiring. The over-65-year-old couples who make up Civic Spirits tend to be community activists who participate in civic events, write newspaper editors, and contact elected officials. Upscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Comfortably Retired > 4819
column7: The members of Comfortably Retired could be poster children for living below one's means. Midscale Mature Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Conservative Couples > 4826
column7: Most of the members of Conservative Couples have retired-at least those who can afford to. Lower Midscale Mature Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Corporate Climbers > 4823
column7: The members of Corporate Climbers are singularly focused on their careers. Upper Midscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Cut-Rate Country > 4832
column7: The rural Boomers in Cut-Rate Country rarely pass up a deal-whether it's getting a sale price at Wal-Mart or using a Discover card for the cash-back feature. Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Domestic Bliss > 4807
column7: Domestic Bliss is home to fashionable couples in their peak earning years. Wealthy Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Economizers > 4855
column7: With nearly all its households earning under $30,000 a year, Economizers is one of the nation's poorest financial groups. These racially mixed singles and single-parent families have few investments or other assets. Downscale Middle Age Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Family Fortunes > 4806
column7: The members of Family Fortunes rank at the top in many financial categories: investing in futures and options, owning mutual funds and U.S. Savings Bonds, and acquiring first mortgages worth over $150,000. Upscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Family Sprawl > 4831
column7: The younger, upper-middle-class families of Family Sprawl make a solid market for financial products ranging from installment credit and U.S. savings bonds to auto and term life insurance. Upper Midscale Younger w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Feathered Nests > 4811
column7: There's money tucked away in Feathered Nests, a collection of middle-aged families with high incomes and above-average investable assets. Wealthy Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Finance Chargers > 4840
column7: Small-town, working-class families characterize Finance Chargers, a segment whose households are asset-light and loan-heavy. Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Financial Independents > 4813
column7: The members of Financial Independents like to go it alone. Upscale Boomers living in suburbia, they trade online, read self-help business books, and find investment ideas in The Wall Street Journal. Upper Midscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Fiscal Rookies > 4829
column7: The young couples and singles of Fiscal Rookies are financially inexperienced Americans. Upper Midscale Younger w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Getting-By Blues > 4854
column7: Life can be a financial challenge in Getting-By Blues. An ethnically diverse segment of 45- to 64-year-olds, they typically rent older apartments in urban and second-city neighborhoods. Low Income Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Globetrotters > 4801
column7: Members of Globetrotters have reached an age-over 65 years old-and a level of financial comfort-many have six-figure incomes-that allow them to indulge their passion for foreign travel. Wealthy Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Golden Agers > 4803
column7: One of the oldest financial segments, Golden Agers is a collection of over-65-year-olds who've amassed substantial levels of IPA. Upscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Greenback Acres > 4844
column7: In Greenback Acres, cash is king. With its lower middle class incomes and low levels of income-producing assets, this segment has relatively few investments, retirement savings, or even credit card debt. Lower Midscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Home Sweet Equity > 4816
column7: Upscale incomes, above average assets, and home-owning couples make this segment an attractive market for large-balance credit products. Upper Midscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Homespun Families > 4843
column7: Homespun Families is a classic country lifestyle. Its 35- to 54-year-old homeowners, including a disproportionate number of farm families, are big fans of pickup trucks, country music, and outdoor sports like hunting and fishing. Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Hunters and Collectors > 4834
column7: It's a world where hunters reign supreme, whether their target is big game, small fish, or rare coins. Hunters & Collectors ranks at the top for collecting coins but near the bottom for most other financial activities. Downscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Khakis and Credit > 4830
column7: They're a mix of families and couples, town and rural folk. But one thing the Boomer households in Khakis & Credit share is a fondness for credit to maintain their middle-class lifestyles. Upper Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Leveraged Life > 4820
column7: They may be upper-middle-class, but Leveraged Life members often maintain that status by living on credit. Upper Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Middle Ages > 4846
column7: The members of Middle Ages paint a portrait of diversity. Racially mixed couples and families, these working-class rural households share low indices for many investment products and banking services. Lower Midscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Midlife Highlife > 4814
column7: Big homes, diversified retirement accounts and high-value life insurance-that's the skinny on Midlife Highlife. Wealthy Middle Age Mostly w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > New Money > 4818
column7: Middle age, upscale suburban and town families make up New Money, a segment of mostly thirty and forty-something households who invest heavily in stocks, futures, and mutual funds. Upper Midscale Younger Mostly w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > New Nests > 4847
column7: Living in small cities and towns, the young families in New Nests are experiencing many firsts. These households rank at the top for acquiring their first mortgages and auto loans. Upper Midscale Younger Mostly w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Old Homesteaders > 4837
column7: Old Homesteaders should not be confused with Old Money. The segment has one of the highest concentrations of nursing home residents in the nation. Downscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Online Living > 4833
column7: No segment scores higher for using Internet Banking than Online Living. This group of mostly 25 to 44-year-old singles, couples, and families ranks number one for stock trading, bill paying, and buying at retail websites. Upper Midscale Younger Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Payday Prospects > 4842
column7: They may earn midscale salaries, but members of the Payday Prospects segment often find themselves living paycheck to paycheck. Midscale Younger Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Paying It Down > 4835
column7: A haven for Generation-Xers pursuing energetic lifestyles, Paying It Down residents rank high for enjoying hard rock, fast cars, and all manner of outdoor activities. Midscale Younger Mostly w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Power Couples > 4804
column7: The most affluent Younger Years segment, Power Couples seems to have it made: six-figure incomes, designer-decorated houses, and high balances in their income-producing assets. Upscale Older w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Retirement Ready > 4828
column7: The nearly-retired Americans in this segment enjoy comfortable lifestyles on middle-class incomes. Midscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Safe at Home > 4824
column7: The members of Safe at Home are aging gracefully in financial comfort. Midscale Middle Age Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Savvy Savers > 4810
column7: The living is easy in Savvy Savers, a segment of well-invested retirees scattered across the nation's suburban and exurban communities. Upper Midscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > School Daze > 4822
column7: A collection of large, suburban households, School Daze represents one of the nation's best markets for borrowing. Upscale Middle Age w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Senior Solitaire > 4827
column7: The elderly singles of Senior Solitaire are America's fiscal conservatives. One of the oldest groups in the nation, they include disproportionate numbers of veterans, widows, and nursing home residents. Lower Midscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Settling Down > 4845
column7: Settling Down contains middle-aged apartment dwellers living mostly in the metropolitan sprawl. A mix of races, ethnicities and family types, members have midscale incomes but low levels of income-producing assets. Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Social Insecurity > 4852
column7: The most downscale of the mature segments, Social Insecurity is filled with ethnically diverse widows and widowers who rely on Social Security and Medicare/Medicaid for survival. Downscale Mature w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Starter Ranches > 4850
column7: They're young, living in small towns, and working class. The households in Starter Ranches tend to have much less income-producing assets than that of the average American-and it shows. Lower Midscale Younger Mostly w/ Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > The Wealth Market > 4800
column7: When it comes to American affluence, The Wealth Market is home to the richest addresses in the nation. Upscale Older Mostly w/o Kids

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Urban Essentials > 4849
column7: The households of Urban Essentials are significant in what they don't do financially. Lower Midscale Older Family Mix

column3: ODC-P Claritas > P$ycle Code > Young Urban Renters > 4856
column7: Young Urban Renters ranks near the bottom for income and income-producing assets. Members of this segment are younger, single, and ethnically diverse. Many are raising small children in one parent households. Low Income Younger Family Mix
